# The settings matrix row, self-driven: "change engine/viewer settings and
# SEE them apply". Two engines are registered (genet.web + genet.livery),
# so picking a viewer is a real choice: the Apparatus pane's radio lowers
# SetViewerOverride, the sidecar persists it, live content RESPAWNS through
# the pinned route, and the Inspector reads the applied engine back off the
# respawned session. Network-dependent (example.com); FRESH profile; the
# restore twin reuses it.
settle 30
key escape

open https://example.com/
settle 30
act Toggle live content
settle 30
assert content-live

# The default route: the static stylo lane.
act Open Inspector pane
settle 5
assert row Engine: genet.web
assert row Viewer: auto

# Retarget through the Apparatus pane: pick the livery lane by name. The
# radio click lowers the typed Action; the respawn applies it visibly.
act Open Apparatus pane
settle 5
assert pane apparatus
click-row genet.livery
settle 30
assert event viewer-changed
assert content-live
assert row Viewer: genet.livery
assert row Engine: genet.livery
capture 01_livery_applied

log settings row (viewer applied via pinned respawn) complete
